My Own Lane is the second studio album by American rapper Kid Ink. The album was released on January 7, 2014, by Tha Alumni Music Group, 88 Classic, and RCA Records. Recording for the album took place during 2013 and finished in November 2013. The album's production was handled by DJ Mustard, Cardiak, The Runners, The Futuristics, Arthur McArthur, soFLY and Nius and Ned Cameron, among others. Kid Ink collaborated with various artists on the album including Chris Brown, Tyga, Pusha T, Elle Varner, Machine Gun Kelly, King Los, Meek Mill, Wale, French Montana, ASAP Ferg and August Alsina, among others. The album was supported by the singles "Show Me" featuring Chris Brown and "Iz U Down" featuring Tyga. - wikipedia -   <a href=" http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/My_Own_Lane" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW"> http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/My_Own_Lane</a>
